The paper discusses the application of deep learning for image restoration in cryo-TEM data, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of neural networks for image restoration is a machine learning (cs.MM) task, and the paper discusses the training of these networks using well-registered pairs of high and low quality images, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of automated downstream processing on restored image data, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks for image restoration, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
